  "text": "The TPD-NH3 profiles ( Figure 12 ) showed two peaks: the first around 208-217 °C and the second around 325-360 °C. The peak at the lower temperature could be attributed to the release of weakly adsorbed NH3, whereas the peak at the higher temperature could be explained by the release of NH3 from NH4 + bound at stronger acid sites [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Figure 12 . TPD-NH3 profiles of the calcined original zeolite and the zeolites produced using different base concentrations.",
